name: integer_i16_binary16_first_lost_negative
description: |
  This is -(2^11 + 1), the first negative integer by magnitude that does not
  survive conversion to binary16 and back. Round-to-nearest maps it to -2^11,
  checking that signed conversion loses precision symmetrically.
format: hex
decode-as: i16-le
pair:
  - with: ../u16/binary16-first-lost-integer.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i16"
  - "binary16"
  - "float-roundtrip"
  - "negative"
  - "precision-loss"
  - "boundary"
---
ff f7   # -2049 (-(2^11 + 1))
